{
  "texts": [
    "If r = 1 we say that the circle ⟨q⟩ is unramified.",
    "The degree s of q as a polynomial in z 1/r is the irregularity s =: Irr(⟨q⟩) of ⟨q⟩ and the quotient s/r =: slope(I) is the slope of ⟨q⟩.",
    "If d ∈ ∂, we denote by I d the fibre of I over the direction d. Taking d as a base point of ∂, the monodromy of I is the automorphism ρ: I d → I d of the fibre I d obtained when going once around ∂ in the positive direction. 2.2.",
    "Formal local systems.",
    "Definition 2.1."
